init_text:
How Worried Should We Be About Screen Time During the Pandemic?

The coronavirus pandemic ended the screen time debate: Screens won. We all now find ourselves on our screens for school, for work and for connecting with family and friends during this time of social distancing and increased isolation.

But should we be worried about this excessive screen use right now? Or should we finally get over it and embrace the benefits of our digital devices?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It's not just the eyes that suffer, it's the body.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'm not saying that we should all go out and run a marathon.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The good news is that we can all take steps to mitigate the negative effects of screen time.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I use Moment on my iPhone and it's a great way to keep track of how much time I spend on my phone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I also use a desktop app called Self Control to block certain websites for a set amount of time.
